## Wiki-specific notes

The wiki is a **separate git repo** at `https://github.com/{{REPO_SLUG}}.wiki.git`, editable by repo collaborators only. It must be enabled **and** have its first page created in the UI before a push works, and the pushing credential must be a classic PAT or `gh` (fine-grained PATs cannot push wikis). If `seed-github.sh` reports it cannot clone the wiki, create that first page and re-run.
<!-- /IF -->

<!-- IF:PROJECT -->
## Project-specific notes

The `{{PROJECT_TITLE}}` Project is created at the owner `$(echo {{REPO_SLUG}} | cut -d/ -f1)` scope, so the credential needs the org/user Projects grant described above even though the issues live in the repo. The script locates the Project by title before creating it, adds each issue as an item, sets the Status/Priority/Size/Level fields from the issue's labels, and posts an "On track" status update — each of those steps is best-effort and skipped with a notice if the Projects grant is missing. See `project-template.md` for the standardized fields, views, and built-in workflows it expects.
